Every Success Story Is A Tale Of Constant Adaptation, Revision, & Change.

Just a Month away from completing 1 year of operations in Jaipur might seems like a Cake Walk for many. But how and what we did CONSISTENTLY & PASSIONATELY noone can understand. 

✅Days of strategic planning. 
✅Targetting 🎯 right people month after month. 
✅Make them aware of newer concepts of Business Group (and Not another kitty group).
✅Hand Holding so many members. 
✅ Doing Workshops to UPSKILL.
And on and on and on ....

Jaipur Chapter has shown Fantastic response and we are Happy to let you know that Jaipur Chapter is now a family of close to 30 Registered ®️ Members and growing 🤞🧿

This April Meet Was FULL HOUSE 🧿
We had to close the bookings as we couldn't accomodate more members. Memebers who wanted to enroll....Cu next month for our 1st Birthday 🎉 Celebration 🎉 (Dates Announcing Soon) 

We also welcome our new Jaipur Moderator Dr. Nitika Jain @dentistinjaipur for taking up this role. Nitika the way you handled the meet this month, while we were stuck in traffic for Hours was commendable. Me & Shweta Jhingran - Co-Admin GWL appreciate your efforts. 

Thanks you all Jaipur members for coming and attending the meet once again and making it super successful. 

Cu Next month everyone in good numbers as we Celebrate 🥳🥂 Our 1st Jaipur Chapter Birthday 🎉

CHEERS 🥂

.
.

Har ki Pauri is the greatest tourist place in Haridwar. This is a bathing ghat on the Ganga which is visited by great spiritual saints, sadhus, and the common man. Brahmakund in Har ki Pauri has the footprint of Lord Vishnu. Ganga Aarti at Har ki Pauri is a 30-45 minute event that is full of devotional energy and spiritual significance. There are innumerable temples in the Har ki Pauri area and this part of Haridwar is generally full of tourists and devotees.
🌟 Don't plan in weekends
🌟 Wear comfortable clothes
🌟Keep water with you
🌟 Check ✅ all routes before plan your trip because
  Lots of traffic ⛔ jam in most of route
#haridwar #vacation #maaganga #harharmahadevॐ

NETWORKING MEET DELHI CHAPTER 
BY Global Women's League 
Global Women's League - Delhi Chapter 

IT WAS NOSTALGIC.....
COMING TO THIS PLACE WHERE WE FIRST LAUNCHED DELHI CHAPTER.....AND NOW FINALLY KICKSTARTING AFTER 4 YEARS.....

We were House full🧿
The event had an overwhelming response, with a full house of buzzing entrepreneurs. It was a lively and energetic atmosphere.

One of the key aspect of the meet was Networking.  As entrepreneurs gathered, they had the opportunity to connect, interact, and build relationships with like-minded individuals. Networking is crucial for growing businesses and finding potential collaborations or partnerships.

The event also focused on upskilling. It's essential for entrepreneurs to continuously enhance their skills and knowledge. By offering workshops or sessions aimed at developing various business-related skills, and we try our best to provide valuable learning opportunities.

I'm sure our workshop on Facebook & Instagram was beneficial for many and members incorporate the tips and suggestions going forward.

Thank you all for showing up and making this meet super successful. We too are equally elated to finally see the DELHI CHAPTER UP AND RUNNING NOW 

Stay Tuned For our Next Meet-up.

Gwl Day Out: Nature, Activities, and Team Building
GWL DAY-OUT: Nature, Activities, and Team Building!

Join us as we step out into the great outdoors for our monthly GWL Day Out! 🌿🌳
We're thrilled to invite you to a fun-filled day packed with exciting activities and opportunities for team building. 
Picture this: a serene picnic spot surrounded by lush greenery, providing the perfect backdrop for a memorable day with your fellow members.

Get ready to connect, bond, and make lasting memories as we engage in a range of activities designed to bring out our competitive spirits and collaborative nature. From relay races and tug-of-war to outdoor fun moments there's something for everyone to enjoy.

But it's not just about the competition! We also believe in fostering a sense of camaraderie and friendship, so be prepared for laughter, conversations, and plenty of candid moments that will make you feel closer than ever with your colleagues.

Of course, we can't forget about the food! A delicious spread of picnic delights awaits us, from mouthwatering snacks to refreshing beverages and beautifully decorated desserts. Don't worry, we've got your taste buds covered!

So, get ready for an unforgettable 
GWL DAY-OUT. Put on your adventure hat, pack some sunscreen, and join us in creating memories that will last a lifetime. #GwlDayOut #PicnicFun #TeamBuilding

See you there, fellow adventurers! 🌿🌼

Are You Still Thinking 💬 Of Visiting @dastkar.delhi 2023? 

Well! Then don't think much and head straight to this place. 

The concept of artisans from different parts of the country coming together to display their handloom and handmade products is truly beautiful. It not only provides a platform for these skilled individuals to showcase their craftsmanship but also gives visitors the opportunity to appreciate and support traditional art forms.

The variety of products available, from handloom sarees to pure woolen clothes such as shawls, stoles, and jackets, indicates the diverse range of offerings. It's wonderful to see such a wide selection of high-quality, handcrafted items. 

The care and skill that goes into creating each piece often makes them truly unique and special💕

Furthermore, the presence of organic and cruelty-free skincare products adds another dimension to the event. It reflects a growing awareness and appreciation for sustainability and ethical practices within the industry. 

Offering such products aligns with the increasing demand for environmentally friendly and conscious consumer choices.

As a visitor, it's a chance to directly engage with the creators and gain insight into the stories behind the products. This personal connection can deepen the appreciation for the items and the people who make them.

On a broader scale, these types of endeavors contribute to the overall cultural landscape by celebrating and preserving heritage crafts.

Must visit from 15th To 26th December

🌟Neelkanth Mahadev Temple, also known as Neelkanth Mandir, is a sacred Hindu temple located in the Pauri Garhwal district of Uttarakhand, India. Situated amidst the lush greenery of the Himalayas, this temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva.

🌟The temple holds great significance in Hindu mythology, as it marks the place where, according to legend, Lord Shiva consumed the poison that emerged from the churning of the cosmic ocean, known as the Samudra Manthan. This act turned his throat blue, earning him the name Neelkanth, which means "blue throat" in Sanskrit
🌟The trek to Neelkanth Mandir often involves a scenic journey through forests, streams, and stunning landscapes, providing a spiritual experience intertwined with natural beauty. The ambiance and spiritual aura of the temple make it a revered destination for religious seekers and nature enthusiasts alike.

Explore Uttarakhand 🌟
Uttarakhand offers a blend of spirituality, adventure, and natural beauty, making it an incredible destination for travelers seeking diverse experiences.
Uttarakhand, located in the lap of the Himalayas, is a beautiful Indian state known for its stunning landscapes, spirituality, and adventure opportunities. Here are some must-visit places and things to do when exploring Uttarakhand
:1. Rishikesh and Haridwar:Spiritual Retreat: Visit these sacred cities along the Ganges River for spirituality, yoga, and ancient temples.Ganga Aarti: Witness the mesmerizing evening aarti (prayer) ceremonies by the river.
2. Mussoorie:Queen of Hills: Enjoy breathtaking views of the Himalayas and explore attractions like Kempty Falls, Gun Hill, and Camel's Back Road.Lal Tibba: Visit the highest peak in Mussoorie for panoramic views.
3. Jim Corbett National Park:Wildlife Safari: Explore the diverse flora and fauna, including Bengal tigers, through safaris.
4. Auli:Skiing: Enjoy skiing in the winter months amidst snow-capped mountains.Scenic Views: Marvel at the stunning views of Himalayan peaks.

Indulgence reached new heights at the extraordinary culinary affair orchestrated by the masterful home chef Chhavi Poddar Lath, the ingenious mind behind Les Delights By Chhavi. 

As we gathered to celebrate the 4th Anniversary of this exquisite brand, the air was redolent with anticipation and excitement for the gastronomic delights to come.

The meticulously curated menu dazzled our palates, weaving a tapestry of flavors and aromas that transported us to the heart of Banaras. 

The pièce de résistance arrived in the form of Chuda Matar and Tamatar chaat - authentic and reminiscent of the culinary heritage of Banaras.
The tantalizing kachori with spicy aloo sabzi, every dish was a symphony of taste. Beetroot cutlet and tacos were nothing short of delectable, captivating our senses with each delightful bite.

Our sweet tooth was lavishly indulged with the unprecedented delights of Paan Pudding and Badam halwa, each dish an ode to innovation and tradition.

Amidst the feast, the air was filled with laughter and conversations, as we reveled in the culinary marvels that graced our tables. Every morsel was savored, and every dish was celebrated, an undeniable testament to the culinary prowess of Chef Chhavi.

It was a memorable collaboration of flavors, experiences, and jubilation. Each dish weaves a narrative of passion and expertise, leaving an indelible mark on our hearts and taste buds. The harmony of flavors and the convivial ambiance made the celebration unforgettable, etching fond memories that will be cherished for years to come💞

Hearty congratulations and heartfelt gratitude to 
Les Delights By Chhavi @lesdelightsbychhavi for gracing us with such an extraordinary culinary experience, and here's to many more years of unparalleled gastronomic innovation and delight!
Cheers 🥂 to a truly incredible celebration that will be fondly remembered, always.

Life as a woman entrepreneur is a journey of resilience, breaking barriers, and embracing the duality of strength in business and grace in life. 
Each challenge is a stepping stone, and every success echoes the power of determination and passion.
🌟Long Working Hours
 Entrepreneurs often find themselves working extended hours, dealing with various aspects of their business, which can lead to burnout.
🌟Decision-Making Pressure
The responsibility of making crucial decisions can be stressful, especially when the outcomes directly impact the success of the business.
🌟Deadline Pressures:
Meeting deadlines and fulfilling business obligations can create a sense of urgency and stress for entrepreneurs.
🌟Financial Worries: Concerns about financial stability and the success of the business can contribute to stress levels.
🌟Family and Personal Commitments: Balancing family obligations with the demands of running a business can be challenging, leading to feelings of guilt or inadequacy.
🌟Isolation: Entrepreneurship can be a lonely journey, and the lack of a traditional support system can intensify stress.Continuous Learning: Keeping up with industry trends and evolving technologies requires ongoing learning, adding to the workload and stress.
🌟Self-Care Challenges: Finding time for self-care activities, such as exercise and relaxation, may be difficult amidst a demanding schedule.
🌟Boundary Setting: Establishing clear boundaries between work and personal life can be challenging, leading to a constant struggle for balance.
 Yes we all face this in our Enterpreneur Journey 🤞
